# Day 06 – Linux File Permissions & TCP vs UDP

## 🎯 Objective

Learn Linux file permissions and understand the differences between TCP and UDP.

---

# 📚 Theory Learned

## Linux File Permissions

Permission Types:

- Read (r)
- Write (w)
- Execute (x)

Permission Categories:

- Owner
- Group
- Others

Common Permission Values:

| Numeric | Permission |
|---------|------------|
| 755 | rwxr-xr-x |
| 644 | rw-r--r-- |
| 600 | rw------- |
| 700 | rwx------ |

---

## TCP

Features:

- Reliable
- Connection-oriented
- Error checking
- Ordered delivery

Examples:

- HTTP
- HTTPS
- SSH
- FTP

---

## UDP

Features:

- Faster
- Connectionless
- No acknowledgement

Examples:

- DNS
- Streaming
- VoIP
- Gaming

---

# 💻 Practical Lab

Linux:

```bash
mkdir PermissionLab
touch notes.txt
touch script.sh
touch secret.txt
ls -l
chmod +x script.sh
chmod -w notes.txt
chmod 755 script.sh
chmod 644 notes.txt
chmod 600 secret.txt
stat notes.txt
```

Networking:

```bash
ss -tuln
netstat -tuln
hostname -I
ip addr
ping google.com
```

